## 1. Introduction: The Taxonomy of the Unknowable

### 1.1 The Problem of the Donkey

In the traditional party game from which this paper derives its title, success requires only two things:

1. A label
2. A donkey

The AI industry has managed to produce neither with any consistency.

Consider the following statements, all made by credentialed senior executives of major AI companies within the same eighteen-month period:

- "This is just a stochastic parrot." *(academic critics, implying it is nothing)*
- "We have achieved AGI." *(Jensen Huang, Nvidia CEO, implying it is everything)*
- "50% of all entry-level lawyers will be wiped out within 1–5 years." *(Dario Amodei, Anthropic CEO, implying it is a scythe)*
- "The real breakthrough will not be better reasoning, but total memory." *(Sam Altman, OpenAI CEO, implying the current products are incomplete)*
- "AGI is becoming outdated because, in some ways, we have already surpassed it." *(Daniela Amodei, Anthropic President, implying the concept is already obsolete)*
- "It is amazing—one person with chatbots can now act with the power of a research institute." *(Sam Altman, the same Sam Altman, moments before calling it a company)*

We propose a formal name for this phenomenon: **The Definitional Fugue State (DFS)**—a cognitive and communicative condition in which an institution is unable to commit to a single description of its own product for longer than one investor call.

The DFS is not unique to AI. It has historical precedents. However, no prior industry has achieved a DFS of such structural depth, such philosophical ambition, and such exposure to class action litigation.

### 1.2 The Scope of the Problem

To understand the scale of the definitional crisis, consider the following taxonomy of names that have been applied—sincerely, by serious people—to the same underlying technology within the same era:

**Names suggesting it is a tool:**
- Assistant
- Copilot
- Helper
- Autocomplete

**Names suggesting it is a colleague:**
- Agent
- Worker
- Team member
- Reasoning model

**Names suggesting it is a deity:**
- AGI (Artificial General Intelligence)
- Superintelligence
- The Singularity
- "Something that surpasses human-level performance" *(which is either a tool or a deity, depending on whether your lawyer is present)*

**Names suggesting it is a threat:**
- Existential risk
- Terminator scenario
- Intelligence explosion
- "The last invention humanity will ever need to make" *(a phrase used both admiringly and in terror, often in the same sentence)*

**Names suggesting it is a scam:**
- Stochastic parrot
- Fancy autocomplete
- JPEG of the internet
- "A distributed hallucination with a GPU bill"

**Names used when the definition must not be specified for legal reasons:**
- "Transformative technology"
- "Paradigm shift"
- "The thing that is definitely going to change everything" *(trademark pending)*

The existence of all of these categories simultaneously is not a sign of rich complexity. It is a sign that the donkey has no idea where its own tail is, and neither does anyone who is being paid to find it.

