## 8. The Black Knight Phase: "The Tail Is Exactly Where We Pinned It"

### 8.1 The Institutional Response to Definitional Challenge

When the definitional game is challenged, the industry deploys what we term the **Semantic Retreat Protocol (SRP)**:

*Step 1:* Acknowledge that some claims were "perhaps overstated in the heat of excitement."

*Step 2:* Insist that the underlying capability is real, even if the specific claim was aspirational.

*Step 3:* Point to a genuine, real use case (like Paul and Rosie) as evidence that the broader claims are directionally correct.

*Step 4:* Announce that the next model will demonstrate what the current model could not.

*Step 5:* Return to the conference circuit.

This is the Black Knight defending the pin's location. Every wound is a "flesh wound." Every failed deployment is a "specific use case mismatch." Every missed capability claim is "we were ahead of our time."

The institution never says: "We pinned the tail on the wrong part of the donkey."

It says: "The donkey has evolved since we described it, and the tail is now correctly positioned for the new donkey."

This is technically a different claim. It is functionally the same game.

### 8.2 The WSJ Headline as Symptom

One of the evidentiary screenshots contains a Wall Street Journal headline: *"Exclusive: OpenAI's top executives are finalizing plans for a major strategy shift to refocus the company around coding and business users."*

The reply tweet reads: *"Headline: OpenAI trying to become Anthropic."*

This is not a joke. This is the PNND game in real time.

A company that was:
- Founded to benefit all of humanity
- Then pivoted to consumer AI
- Then pivoted to enterprise AI
- Then pivoted to safety-focused AI
- Then pivoted to AGI
- Then pivoted to infrastructure
- Is now pivoting to coding and business users

Each pivot requires a new name for what the company is. Each new name for what the company is requires a new name for what the product is. Each new name for the product requires a new donkey.

There is no stable donkey. There is only the perpetual motion of the blindfold.

