### 9.1 The Inescapable Inside, Again

This paper was written with the assistance of a large language model.

A large language model is a product whose fundamental nature this paper has just spent nine sections arguing is deliberately undefined.

Therefore, this paper has been co-authored by something that cannot decide whether it is a tool, an assistant, an agent, a reasoning system, an intelligence, or a very expensive autocomplete.

This is the **Inescapable Inside** of the anthology's three-act structure. Every paper that critiques the AI industry using AI tools is structurally contaminated by the critique it delivers.

### 9.2 The Specific Contamination

The recursive contamination here is precise:

This paper argues that the AI industry's definitional chaos is a strategic choice that enables false advertising.

This paper was written by a tool that markets itself with the word "Claude"—a name that implies personhood, implies a stable identity, implies an entity rather than a process.

